        <h1>Department of Civil Society and the Voluntary Sector</h1>
        
        <div class="pageDescription"><p>The Department of Civil Society and the Voluntary Sector is responsible for the overall coordination of the state’s relationship with the voluntary sector, including the administration of cross-sectoral grant schemes in the voluntary field and the current responsibility for taking strategic decision in order to strengthen the voluntary sector. Moreover the department‘s portfolio includes business and culture, social inclusion and poverty alleviation, culture in the work place, dialogue between different religious and life stance communities, administration and further development of grant schemes for religious communities outside of the Church of Norway, volunteer centres, grant schemes for local voluntary work (Frifond), the Voluntary Register (Frivillighetsregisteret), the Fundraising Register (Innsamlingsregisteret), reports, analyses, research and producing statistics.</p></div>        
